      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HUXTON NZ (9) was a beaten favourite when resuming in this grade but the effort still had merit, finishing 3.7 metres away at this circuit and distance. Drawn to enjoy a trail and has won when second-up before so should be improved. Can atone. PETES CRUNCH TIME (3) has been racing at Menangle and while he didn't feature in his last two outings he was runner-up prior. Suited returning to a venue where he strikes at 50 per cent and should enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. MAJOR REASON (2) led from a similar draw to this and went on for a Penrith win the last time he started on the front line last month. COOL NIGHT (11) may need luck from this draw but has some decent efforts under the belt including a win here last month.",
